###  DEPARTMENT ENDPOINTS

### Create Department
POST http://localhost:8080/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "IT",
  "description": "Information Technology Department"
}

### Create another Department
POST http://localhost:8080/api/departments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "HR",
  "description": "Human Resources Department"
}

### Get All Departments
GET http://localhost:8080/api/departments

### Get Department by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/departments/1

### Update Department
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/departments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "IT Updated",
  "description": "Updated IT Department"
}

### Delete Department
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/departments/2


--- EMPLOYEE ENDPOINTS --

### Create Employee (make sure department with ID 1 exists first)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@imbank.com",
  "salary": 75000.00,
  "departmentId": 1
}

### Create another Employee
POST http://localhost:8080/api/employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@imbank.com",
  "salary": 82000.00,
  "departmentId": 1
}

### Get All Employees
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees

### Get Employee by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1

### Get Employees by Department
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/department/1

### Update Employee
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/employees/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@imbank.com",
  "salary": 85000.00,
  "departmentId": 1
}

### Delete Employee
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/employees/2


### Get employees by salary range
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/salary-range?min=50000&max=80000

### Get employees by department name
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/by-department-name?name=IT

### Get employees with above average salary
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/above-average-salary

### Search employees by name
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/search?keyword=john

### Get employees paginated (default: page 0, size 10, sort by id asc)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/paginated

### Get employees paginated - page 1, size 5
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/paginated?page=1&size=5

### Get employees sorted by salary descending
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/paginated?sortBy=salary&sortDir=desc

### Get employees sorted by fullName ascending, page 0, size 3
GET http://localhost:8080/api/employees/paginated?page=0&size=3&sortBy=fullName&sortDir=asc

createdAt / updatedAt — entity auditing
Custom queries (JPQL) — repository level
Pagination & Sorting — extends queries
Application Properties & Profiles — e.g., default base salary, min salary, environment-specific configs
AWS Database setup — last, swap H2 for real DB